conditional Statements:
*To make the set of instructions execute only when the given condition is true
*used to delete wheather the code has to be executed or skip based on the given condition
*line-line(sequence)
block of code: set of instructions
execute only at specific condition

condition: an expression that evaluates that evaluates a result(t or f)
ex:console.log(5>6)
Methods:
if
if-else
else if
switch ternary operator

if:only one possible condition
*if the condition is true it will executes otherwise it skips
syntax:
if(condition){
block of code
}

ex:
 1.      let a=4
       let b=5
       if(a<b){
        document.write("hello Reddy","<br>")
       }
       document.write("brilliant chiru")
output:
hello Reddy
brilliant chiru

2. condition false
       let a=4
       let b=5
       if(a>b){
        document.write("hello Reddy","<br>")
       }
       document.write("brilliant chiru")

output:
brilliant chiru

Else:
Ex:  
      let a=4
       let b=5
       if(a>b){
        document.write("hello Reddy","<br>")
       }else{
        document.write("hi sam")

       }
       document.write("brilliant chiru")
op:
hi sambrilliant chiru

else-if:
ex:

      let age=prompt("enter your age")
        let name=("enter your name")
        if(age<18){
            alert(name+"you are too young to marry")
        
        }
        else if(age>35){
            alert(name+"you are too old to marry")

        }else{
            alert(name+"perfect age  to marry")
        }
        alert("welcome to my world")


 
 
